<div class="column__4 mediumColumn__12 largeColumn__10 ">
  
  
<h1 class="stdPage__title">In the news</h1>


</div>
</div>
</header>
<div class="slice--light">
<div class="container">
<div class="column__4 mediumColumn__3 colL">

</div>
<div class="column__4 mediumColumn__8 largeColumn__8">
<div class="pageContent pageContent--std">

<p>The Saw Swee Hock Student Centre (SAW), LSE&rsquo;s latest landmark building, has transformed the campus, with the Students&rsquo; Union and student-focused departments of the School taking up residence.</p>
<p>The first new building LSE has commissioned in over 40 years, SAW's dramatic sculptural form and unusual perforated brick fa&ccedil;ade was designed by Irish architect O&rsquo;Donnell + Tuomey. Since opening its doors on 6 January 2014 it has steadily been garnering praise from students, staff and architecture critics alike.</p>
<p>Critics have called the building &ldquo;richly considered and finished&rdquo;, &ldquo;eccentric and deeply satisfying&rdquo;, &ldquo;fantastically individual&rdquo; and &ldquo;a fold-out marvel [and] lesson in architectural origami&rdquo;. To read more, see below:&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>


<div class="accordionContainer">



